.Im MicroEmacs macro;function;bitwise
.so me.tni
.TH &band 4
.XI &band - "Bitwise AND operator"
.XI &bor  - "Bitwise OR operator"
.XI &bxor  - "Bitwise XOR operator"
.XI &bnot - "Bitwise NOT operator"
.SH NAME
&band, &bor, &bnot, &bxor \- Bitwise macro operators
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B &band
.I num1
.I num2
.br
.B &bor
.I num1
.I num2
.br
.B &bxor
.I num1
.I num2
.br
.B &bnot
.I num
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
The bitwise  operators  perform bit  operations on numeric values  returning a
numerical result of the operation.
.PP
The functions may all be abbreviated to their three letter  abbreviation (i.e.
\fB&band\fR  may be expressed as  \fB&ban\fR). In all cases the first argument
is completely evaluated before the second argument.
.IP "\fB&band \fInum1\fR \fInum2\fR"
Bitwise AND of \fInum1\fR and \fInum2\fR i.e. \fInum1\fR & \fInum2\fR.
.IP "\fB&bor\fR \fInum1\fR \fInum2\fR"
Bitwise  (inclusive)  OR  of  \fInum1\fR  and  \fInum2\fR  i.e.  \fInum1\fR  |
\fInum2\fR.
.IP "\fB&bxor\fR \fInum1\fR \fInum2\fR"
Bitwise  (exclusive OR) XOR of \fInum1\fR  and  \fInum2\fR  i.e.  \fInum1\fR ^
\fInum2\fR.
.IP "\fB&not\fR \fInum\fR"
Bitwise  NOT  operator  of  \fInum\fR,  inverts  the  state  of all bits  i.e.
~\fInum\fR.
.LP
Evaluation of the bitwise  operators are left to right, the leftmost  argument
is fully evaluated  before the next argument. The operator  ordering is prefix
notation (see
.Ht &add 4
for an example of prefix ordering).
